record.title: Gallipoli Mosque (Building)
record.detail: Place of worship built by Ahmet Asim largely with funds raised from Sydney's Turkish community, on the site of a previous mosque in a converted house.

record.title: Louise Hawson
record.detail: 52 Suburbs is the name of a project created by writer and photographer Louise Hawson. Realising she was a stranger in her own city, Sydney, Louise set herself the task of exploring one new Sydney suburb a week for 52 weeks, 'in search of the beauty in the 'burb'. The project is presented in blog format with photographic diptychs 'telling' the story of her travels.

record.title: Some
record.detail: The Auburn Gallipoli Mosque officially opened in 1999, 20 years after the first mosque on the site opened for worship. The local Turkish community, which initiated and funded the building, makes up about half of the present congregation. The remainder are Muslims from other ethnic backgrounds.

record.title: Auburn

record.title: Immigration

record.title: Religion
record.detail: Religion has had a profound influence on the geography, culture, politics, and artistic life of Sydney. While religion has mostly been a conservative force, preserving traditions transported from home societies, it has also reflected the setting and people of Sydney, its harbour, bushland and suburbs.
